Prince Charles, 71 has tested positive for Coronavirus though he remains in “good health.” Due to the report, both Charles and Camilla are now self-isolating at Balmoral, the report adds. Buckingham Palace said the Queen last saw her son on 12 March, but also "remains in good health". BBC quoted a Clarence House statement which read: "In accordance with government and medical advice, the prince and the duchess are now self-isolating at home in Scotland.